	 <title>System.ProcessID</title> 
	 <para></para> 
	 <bridgehead renderas="sect3">Remarks</bridgehead> 
	 <para>This operator returns the ID of the current process. This operator is
		  non-deterministic unless called within the same process.</para> 
	 <example> 
		  <title>Example</title> 
		  <programlisting>select Processes where ID = ProcessID();</programlisting> 
		  <programlisting>ID   Session_ID UseDTC 
---- ---------- ------ 
1934 1          False</programlisting> 
		  <para>Note: This is just an example, results will probably vary.</para>
		  
	 </example> 
